commit.message:
Make `bc`/`dc` just exit immediately when failing to write to stdout

This prevents a stack overflow, as well as making things cleaner and
more consistent.

commit.message:
Improve the fix from last commit

It turns out, obviously, that ignoring errors on flush will prevent any
error message from being printed. This goes against the `bc` standard,
as the same user pointed out to me. Whoops.

The proper fix might be to move the `bc_vm_atexit()` call to *before*
the last `setjmp()` clears. This commit is that fix; I will confirm with
the user.

This reverts last commit as well.

Signed-off-by: Gavin D. Howard <gavin@gavinhoward.com>

verification.payload:
tree 80257586b68fbf66c945e9f913b9215ad97ee51f
parent 235482c16dd31e8e3ad5781a855d39cdbe2847ab
author Gavin D. Howard <gavin@gavinhoward.com> 1710257233 -0600
committer Gavin D. Howard <gavin@gavinhoward.com> 1710257233 -0600

Improve the fix from last commit

It turns out, obviously, that ignoring errors on flush will prevent any
error message from being printed. This goes against the `bc` standard,
as the same user pointed out to me. Whoops.

The proper fix might be to move the `bc_vm_atexit()` call to *before*
the last `setjmp()` clears. This commit is that fix; I will confirm with
the user.

This reverts last commit as well.

Signed-off-by: Gavin D. Howard <gavin@gavinhoward.com>

commit.message:
Fix a bug found by a user

This bug is that an error can happen when flushing the streams on exit,
and in that case, `bc`/`dc` will jump out, but there won't be any
jmp_buf stack, so crash.

I can't reproduce it, but I'm pretty sure this is the fix, and I will
confirm with the reporter.

Signed-off-by: Gavin D. Howard <gavin@gavinhoward.com>

verification.payload:
tree 62e93975c1a53c381c05aa75de7b5b2500b23aa3
parent 133bff368551a31f1ccde4b1df7b5470ff30d014
author Gavin D. Howard <gavin@gavinhoward.com> 1710212496 -0600
committer Gavin D. Howard <gavin@gavinhoward.com> 1710212496 -0600

Fix a bug found by a user

This bug is that an error can happen when flushing the streams on exit,
and in that case, `bc`/`dc` will jump out, but there won't be any
jmp_buf stack, so crash.

I can't reproduce it, but I'm pretty sure this is the fix, and I will
confirm with the reporter.

Signed-off-by: Gavin D. Howard <gavin@gavinhoward.com>
